"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The issue with the code is that it tries to plot datetime objects directly on the x-axis. Matplotlib requires numerical values for plotting, not datetime objects. Also, when adding text to the plot using plt.text(), the first two arguments should be numerical coordinates, not a string date.\",\n  \"patch\": \"15c15\\n<ax.plot(df['C'], df['E'])\\n---\\n>ax.plot_date(df['C'], df['E'])\\n\\n17c17\\n<plt.text(\\\"2013-01-05\\\", 0.5, \\\"SAMPLE\\\")\\n---\\n>plt.text(datetime.datetime(2013, 1, 5), 0.5, \\\"SAMPLE\\\")\"\n}"